-- JSS1 (8 questions)
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS1', 'HARD', 'Living Things', 'Classification', 'Which of the following is NOT a characteristic of living things?', '{"Growth","Movement","Photosynthesis","Reproduction"}'::text[], 2, 'Photosynthesis is a process carried out by plants, not a characteristic of all living things. The basic characteristics are movement, respiration, growth, reproduction, etc.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS1', 'HARD', 'Living Things', 'Cells', 'The basic unit of structure and function in all living organisms is the:', '{"Tissue","Organ","Cell","Nucleus"}'::text[], 2, 'The cell is the fundamental unit of life. Tissues are groups of cells, organs are groups of tissues.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS1', 'HARD', 'Living Things', 'Sense Organs', 'The part of the eye that controls the amount of light entering is the:', '{"Retina","Pupil","Iris","Lens"}'::text[], 2, 'The iris controls the size of the pupil, which regulates the amount of light entering the eye.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS1', 'VERY_HARD', 'Health', 'Diseases', 'Which vitamin deficiency causes rickets in children?', '{"Vitamin A","Vitamin C","Vitamin D","Vitamin B12"}'::text[], 2, 'Rickets is caused by Vitamin D deficiency, leading to softening and weakening of bones.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS1', 'HARD', 'Environment', 'Pollution', 'The type of pollution caused by excessive noise from generators and loudspeakers is called:', '{"Air pollution","Water pollution","Noise pollution","Land pollution"}'::text[], 2, 'Noise pollution is unwanted or excessive sound that can harm human health and the environment.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS1', 'HARD', 'Living Things', 'Reproduction', 'The male reproductive cell in flowering plants is called:', '{"Ovule","Pollen grain","Style","Anther"}'::text[], 1, 'Pollen grains contain the male gametes in flowering plants. Ovules contain the female gametes.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS1', 'HARD', 'Matter', 'States', 'The change of state from solid directly to gas is called:', '{"Melting","Evaporation","Sublimation","Condensation"}'::text[], 2, 'Sublimation is the direct change from solid to gas (e.g., dry ice, camphor).', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS1', 'VERY_HARD', 'Energy', 'Forms', 'The energy possessed by a moving car is an example of:', '{"Potential energy","Chemical energy","Kinetic energy","Nuclear energy"}'::text[], 2, 'Kinetic energy is the energy of motion. A moving car has kinetic energy.', 'MCQ', 2, true),

-- JSS2 (9 questions)
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS2', 'HARD', 'Human Body', 'Digestive System', 'The enzyme in the mouth that begins the digestion of starch is called:', '{"Pepsin","Amylase","Lipase","Trypsin"}'::text[], 1, 'Salivary amylase (ptyalin) begins the digestion of starch into maltose in the mouth.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS2', 'HARD', 'Human Body', 'Circulatory System', 'The largest artery in the human body is the:', '{"Pulmonary artery","Aorta","Carotid artery","Femoral artery"}'::text[], 1, 'The aorta is the largest artery, carrying oxygenated blood from the left ventricle to the rest of the body.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS2', 'HARD', 'Human Body', 'Respiratory System', 'During inhalation, the diaphragm:', '{"Relaxes and moves up","Contracts and flattens","Stays still","Moves sideways"}'::text[], 1, 'During inhalation, the diaphragm contracts and flattens, increasing chest volume and drawing air into the lungs.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS2', 'VERY_HARD', 'Living Things', 'Ecology', 'An organism that hunts and eats other organisms is called a:', '{"Prey","Predator","Scavenger","Decomposer"}'::text[], 1, 'A predator is an organism that hunts and kills other organisms (prey) for food.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS2', 'HARD', 'Matter', 'Atoms', 'The smallest particle of an element that can take part in a chemical reaction is:', '{"Molecule","Atom","Electron","Proton"}'::text[], 1, 'An atom is the smallest particle of an element that retains its chemical properties.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS2', 'HARD', 'Forces', 'Friction', 'Friction can be reduced by using:', '{"Sandpaper","Rough surfaces","Lubricants","Heavy weights"}'::text[], 2, 'Lubricants like oil and grease reduce friction by creating a slippery layer between surfaces.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS2', 'HARD', 'Energy', 'Sources', 'Which of these is a non-renewable energy source?', '{"Solar","Wind","Natural gas","Hydroelectric"}'::text[], 2, 'Natural gas is a fossil fuel formed over millions of years and is non-renewable. Solar, wind, and hydro are renewable.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS2', 'VERY_HARD', 'Human Body', 'Excretory System', 'The organ that filters waste products from the blood to produce urine is the:', '{"Liver","Lungs","Kidney","Skin"}'::text[], 2, 'The kidneys filter waste products like urea from the blood and produce urine. The liver detoxifies chemicals.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS2', 'HARD', 'Environment', 'Conservation', 'Bush burning is harmful because it:', '{"Kills soil microorganisms and destroys habitats","Increases soil fertility","Causes rainfall","Creates more farmland"}'::text[], 0, 'Bush burning kills soil organisms, destroys habitats, releases carbon dioxide, and can lead to soil erosion.', 'MCQ', 2, true),

-- JSS3 (8 questions)
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS3', 'HARD', 'Chemistry', 'Elements', 'The horizontal rows in the Periodic Table are called:', '{"Groups","Periods","Families","Blocks"}'::text[], 1, 'Rows in the Periodic Table are called periods. Vertical columns are called groups or families.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS3', 'HARD', 'Human Body', 'Nervous System', 'The three main parts of the brain are the:', '{"Cerebrum, cerebellum, medulla oblongata","Frontal, parietal, temporal","Neurons, axons, dendrites","Gray matter, white matter, spinal cord"}'::text[], 0, 'The three main parts are the cerebrum (thinking), cerebellum (coordination), and medulla oblongata (automatic functions).', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS3', 'VERY_HARD', 'Chemistry', 'Reactions', 'The reaction between an acid and a base to form salt and water is called:', '{"Oxidation","Reduction","Neutralization","Hydrolysis"}'::text[], 2, 'Neutralization is the reaction between an acid and a base producing salt and water.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS3', 'HARD', 'Energy', 'Electricity', 'The unit of electric current is:', '{"Volt","Ampere","Ohm","Watt"}'::text[], 1, 'Electric current is measured in amperes (amps). Voltage is in volts, resistance in ohms, power in watts.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS3', 'HARD', 'Living Things', 'Genetics', 'The thread-like structures in the nucleus that carry genetic information are:', '{"Chromosomes","Ribosomes","Mitochondria","Lysosomes"}'::text[], 0, 'Chromosomes carry DNA and genetic information. Ribosomes make proteins, mitochondria produce energy.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS3', 'HARD', 'Human Body', 'Endocrine System', 'The master gland that controls other endocrine glands is the:', '{"Thyroid gland","Pituitary gland","Adrenal gland","Pancreas"}'::text[], 1, 'The pituitary gland in the brain controls many other endocrine glands and is called the master gland.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS3', 'VERY_HARD', 'Light', 'Optics', 'The splitting of white light into its component colors is called:', '{"Reflection","Refraction","Diffraction","Dispersion"}'::text[], 3, 'Dispersion is the splitting of white light into its constituent colors (ROYGBIV) through a prism.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('BASIC SCIENCE', 'JSS3', 'HARD', 'Environment', 'Ecosystem', 'The process by which green plants make their own food using sunlight is:', '{"Transpiration","Photosynthesis","Respiration","Fermentation"}'::text[], 1, 'Photosynthesis uses sunlight, carbon dioxide, and water to produce glucose and oxygen.', 'MCQ', 2, true)

