('ENGLISH', 'PRIMARY', 'HARD', 'Comprehension', 'Main Idea', '"The baobab tree is often called the Tree of Life. Its fruit is rich in vitamin C, its leaves can be eaten as vegetables, and its bark can be used to make rope and cloth." The main idea is:', '{"Baobab trees are very tall","Baobab trees have many useful parts","Baobab fruit tastes good","Baobab bark makes rope"}'::text[], 1, 'The passage emphasizes multiple uses of the baobab tree, not just one specific use.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('ENGLISH', 'PRIMARY', 'HARD', 'Grammar', 'Tenses', 'Which sentence is in the future perfect tense?', '{"I will go to school","I have gone to school","I will have finished my homework by 5pm","I was going to school"}'::text[], 2, 'Future perfect: will have + past participle. "Will have finished" shows an action completed before a future time.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('ENGLISH', 'PRIMARY', 'HARD', 'Vocabulary', 'Root Words', 'The root word in "unhappiness" is:', '{"un","happy","ness","unhappy"}'::text[], 1, '"Happy" is the root word. "Un-" is a prefix, "-ness" is a suffix.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('ENGLISH', 'PRIMARY', 'VERY_HARD', 'Grammar', 'Active vs Passive', 'Change to active voice: "The food was cooked by Mama."', '{"The food was cooked","Mama cooked the food","Cooking was done by Mama","Mama was cooking"}'::text[], 1, 'Active voice: subject (Mama) performs the action (cooked) on object (food).', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('ENGLISH', 'PRIMARY', 'HARD', 'Comprehension', 'Inference', '"The sky grew dark. Thunder rumbled in the distance. People rushed to bring in their laundry." What was about to happen?', '{"A parade","A storm","Sunset","A festival"}'::text[], 1, 'Dark sky, thunder, and people hurrying to bring in laundry all indicate an approaching storm.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('ENGLISH', 'PRIMARY', 'HARD', 'Punctuation', 'Quotation Marks', 'Which sentence uses quotation marks correctly?', '{"She said hello.","She said, hello.","She said, Hello!","She said Hello!"}'::text[], 2, 'Quotation marks go around the exact words spoken, with a comma before the quote. Option C shows the correct format: She said, "Hello!"', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('ENGLISH', 'PRIMARY', 'VERY_HARD', 'Grammar', 'Conditionals', 'If I _____ rich, I would travel the world.', '{"am","was","were","will be"}'::text[], 2, 'Second conditional uses "if + were" for unreal present situations. "If I were rich, I would..."', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('ENGLISH', 'PRIMARY', 'HARD', 'Writing', 'Paragraphs', 'Which sentence does NOT belong in a paragraph about the importance of reading?', '{"Reading improves vocabulary","Reading increases knowledge","Football is a popular sport","Reading develops critical thinking"}'::text[], 2, 'Football is unrelated to the topic of reading importance.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('ENGLISH', 'PRIMARY', 'HARD', 'Vocabulary', 'Compound Words', 'Which word is a compound word?', '{"Running","Teacher","Sunflower","Quickly"}'::text[], 2, 'Sunflower = sun + flower. It is a compound word made of two smaller words.', 'MCQ', 2, true),
('ENGLISH', 'PRIMARY', 'HARD', 'Literature', 'Figures of Speech', '"The wind whispered through the trees" is an example of:', '{"Simile","Metaphor","Personification","Alliteration"}'::text[], 2, 'Personification gives human qualities (whispered) to non-human things (wind).', 'MCQ', 2, true)

ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
